    <item>
      <title>What Is Killing Landscape</title>
      <description>In Buddhism, “Killing” is defined by the technical mechanics of the mind, not by social laws. The unwholesome Kamma is complete only if five factors are present. This talk explores the deeper meaning of killing in relation to landscapes, nature, intention, and Theravāda teachings.</description>
      <link>https://americanmonk.org/</link>
