    <item>
      <title>Why Is Halloween Bad According to Theravāda Buddhism?</title>
      <description>Bhante Subhūti explains why Halloween is considered unwholesome in Theravāda Buddhism, showing how dressing up and acting can create future kamma and influence rebirth. He also shares how the power of mettā can truly protect one from fear and spirits.</description>
